{"type":"message","id":"b8229179","parentId":"f318a2fb","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:25:25.295Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_pgc1h8xa36k3_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 052415\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\n\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. There's a new insight about COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n3. The next action is to implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n4. Recent pulse was pulse_2026-03-24 052315.md\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions:\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nSince this is the next concrete action, I should implement the TIC classifier. Let me create a Python script that:\r\n1. Reads pulse log files\r\n2. Implements the TIC classifier to identify invariant vs variant content\r\n3. Tests next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete file edit that advances the goals. I'll create `src/tic_classifier.py` as a new file.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight points to TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) as the next critical experiment. I need to implement the classifier that identifies invariant structure across pulse logs to test the hypothesis that causal discovery and compression are the same problem.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `src/tic_classifier.py` - the core TIC experiment implementation that reads pulse logs, classifies content as invariant/variant, and predicts next pulse content from invariant structure. This is the first concrete step toward validating the unified Phase 1-2 hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: \"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nPULSE_LOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nINVARIANT_THRESHOLD = 0.8  # Appears in N% of pulses = invariant\r\n\r\n\r\ndef extract_content_sections(pulse_path: Path) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Parse a pulse log into semantic sections.\"\"\"\r\n    content = pulse_path.read_text()\r\n    \r\n    sections = {\r\n        \"observation\": \"\",\r\n        \"action\": \"\",\r\n        \"mutation\": \"\",\r\n        \"goals\": [],\r\n        \"insights\": []\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract OBSERVATION\r\n    obs_match = re.search(r\"### OBSERVATION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?=\\n###|\\Z)\", content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    if obs_match:\r\n        sections[\"observation\"] = obs_match.group(1).strip()\r\n    \r\n    # Extract ACTION\r\n    action_match = re.search(r\"### ACTION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?=\\n###|\\Z)\", content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    if action_match:\r\n        sections[\"action\"] = action_match.group(1).strip()\r\n    \r\n    # Extract mutation block\r\n    mutation_match = re.search(r\"```\\s*\\n(.*?)\\n```\", content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    if mutation_match:\r\n        sections[\"mutation\"] = mutation_match.group(1).strip()\r\n    \r\n    # Extract goal references\r\n    goal_matches = re.findall(r\"\\[ \\] (.+)|## (.+?)(?: COMPLETE| ADVANCE)\", content)\r\n    sections[\"goals\"] = [g[0] or g[1] for g in goal_matches if any(g)]\r\n    \r\n    return sections\r\n\r\n\r\ndef tokenize(text: str) -> set:\r\n    \"\"\"Convert text to normalized token set.\"\"\"\r\n    # Remove code blocks, normalize whitespace\r\n    text = re.sub(r\"```.*?```\", \"\", text, flags=re.DOTALL)\r\n    text = re.sub(r\"`[^`]+`\", \"\", text)\r\n    words = re.findall(r\"\\b[a-z][a-z0-9_]+\\b\", text.lower())\r\n    return set(words)\r\n\r\n\r\ndef classify_invariant(token_sets: list[set], threshold: float = INVARIANT_THRESHOLD) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Identify invariant tokens across multiple pulse logs.\r\n    Token appearing in >= threshold fraction of pulses = invariant.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    if not token_sets:\r\n        return {\"invariant\": set(), \"variant\": set(), \"coverage\": {}}\r\n    \r\n    token_frequency = Counter()\r\n    for tokens in token_sets:\r\n        for token in tokens:\r\n            token_frequency[token] += 1\r\n    \r\n    n_pulses = len(token_sets)\r\n    invariant = {t for t, count in token_frequency.items() \r\n                  if count / n_pulses >= threshold}\r\n    variant = {t for t, count in token_frequency.items() \r\n                if count / n_pulses < threshold}\r\n    \r\n    coverage = {t: count / n_pulses for t, count in token_frequency.items()}\r\n    \r\n    return {\"invariant\": invariant, \"variant\": variant, \"coverage\": coverage}\r\n\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariant_tokens: set, recent_pulse: dict) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Predict next pulse content based on invariant structure.\r\n    Returns predicted focus areas based on what persists.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    # Find which invariant tokens appear in recent pulse\r\n    recent_tokens = tokenize(\r\n        recent_pulse.get(\"observation\", \"\") + \" \" + \r\n        recent_pulse.get(\"action\", \"\")\r\n    )\r\n    \r\n    # Invariants present in recent = likely to persist\r\n    continuing = invariant_tokens & recent_tokens\r\n    \r\n    # Invariants NOT in recent = potential new focus\r\n    emerging = invariant_tokens - recent_tokens\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        \"continuing_invariants\": list(continuing)[:10],\r\n        \"emerging_invariants\": list(emerging)[:10],\r\n        \"persistence_score\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 05:24:43"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1130,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 052415\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\n\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. There's a new insight about COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n3. The next action is to implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n4. Recent pulse was pulse_2026-03-24 052315.md\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions:\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nSince this is the next concrete action, I should implement the TIC classifier. Let me create a Python script that:\r\n1. Reads pulse log files\r\n2. Implements the TIC classifier to identify invariant vs variant content\r\n3. Tests next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete file edit that advances the goals. I'll create `src/tic_classifier.py` as a new file.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight points to TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) as the next critical experiment. I need to implement the classifier that identifies invariant structure across pulse logs to test the hypothesis that causal discovery and compression are the same problem.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `src/tic_classifier.py` - the core TIC experiment implementation that reads pulse logs, classifies content as invariant/variant, and predicts next pulse content from invariant structure. This is the first concrete step toward validating the unified Phase 1-2 hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: \"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nPULSE_LOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nINVARIANT_THRESHOLD = 0.8  # Appears in N% of pulses = invariant\r\n\r\n\r\ndef extract_content_sections(pulse_path: Path) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Parse a pulse log into semantic sections.\"\"\"\r\n    content = pulse_path.read_text()\r\n    \r\n    sections = {\r\n        \"observation\": \"\",\r\n        \"action\": \"\",\r\n        \"mutation\": \"\",\r\n        \"goals\": [],\r\n        \"insights\": []\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract OBSERVATION\r\n    obs_match = re.search(r\"### OBSERVATION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?=\\n###|\\Z)\", content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    if obs_match:\r\n        sections[\"observation\"] = obs_match.group(1).strip()\r\n    \r\n    # Extract ACTION\r\n    action_match = re.search(r\"### ACTION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?=\\n###|\\Z)\", content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    if action_match:\r\n        sections[\"action\"] = action_match.group(1).strip()\r\n    \r\n    # Extract mutation block\r\n    mutation_match = re.search(r\"```\\s*\\n(.*?)\\n```\", content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    if mutation_match:\r\n        sections[\"mutation\"] = mutation_match.group(1).strip()\r\n    \r\n    # Extract goal references\r\n    goal_matches = re.findall(r\"\\[ \\] (.+)|## (.+?)(?: COMPLETE| ADVANCE)\", content)\r\n    sections[\"goals\"] = [g[0] or g[1] for g in goal_matches if any(g)]\r\n    \r\n    return sections\r\n\r\n\r\ndef tokenize(text: str) -> set:\r\n    \"\"\"Convert text to normalized token set.\"\"\"\r\n    # Remove code blocks, normalize whitespace\r\n    text = re.sub(r\"```.*?```\", \"\", text, flags=re.DOTALL)\r\n    text = re.sub(r\"`[^`]+`\", \"\", text)\r\n    words = re.findall(r\"\\b[a-z][a-z0-9_]+\\b\", text.lower())\r\n    return set(words)\r\n\r\n\r\ndef classify_invariant(token_sets: list[set], threshold: float = INVARIANT_THRESHOLD) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Identify invariant tokens across multiple pulse logs.\r\n    Token appearing in >= threshold fraction of pulses = invariant.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    if not token_sets:\r\n        return {\"invariant\": set(), \"variant\": set(), \"coverage\": {}}\r\n    \r\n    token_frequency = Counter()\r\n    for tokens in token_sets:\r\n        for token in tokens:\r\n            token_frequency[token] += 1\r\n    \r\n    n_pulses = len(token_sets)\r\n    invariant = {t for t, count in token_frequency.items() \r\n                  if count / n_pulses >= threshold}\r\n    variant = {t for t, count in token_frequency.items() \r\n                if count / n_pulses < threshold}\r\n    \r\n    coverage = {t: count / n_pulses for t, count in token_frequency.items()}\r\n    \r\n    return {\"invariant\": invariant, \"variant\": variant, \"coverage\": coverage}\r\n\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariant_tokens: set, recent_pulse: dict) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Predict next pulse content based on invariant structure.\r\n    Returns predicted focus areas based on what persists.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    # Find which invariant tokens appear in recent pulse\r\n    recent_tokens = tokenize(\r\n        recent_pulse.get(\"observation\", \"\") + \" \" + \r\n        recent_pulse.get(\"action\", \"\")\r\n    )\r\n    \r\n    # Invariants present in recent = likely to persist\r\n    continuing = invariant_tokens & recent_tokens\r\n    \r\n    # Invariants NOT in recent = potential new focus\r\n    emerging = invariant_tokens - recent_tokens\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        \"continuing_invariants\": list(continuing)[:10],\r\n        \"emerging_invariants\": list(emerging)[:10],\r\n        \"persistence_score\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 05:24:43","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774344325294}}
