{"type":"message","id":"306035a0","parentId":"f6236c13","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:25:47.456Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_48mxo2fxnnwl_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 052515\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: src/tic_classifier.py (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the most impactful next action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals, I have:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 complete (Architecture cross-analysis and integration spec)\r\n2. Gap-Decay synthesis complete\r\n3. LLM-Augmented Pulse complete\r\n4. Pending items include: PowerShell wrapper, significance scoring, λ tuning, wiring to TemporalAttention backend, compression ratio measurement\r\n5. Current focus: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - Phase 1 advancement\r\n6. NEXT ACTION: TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n   - Implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n   - Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n   - Predict next pulse content\r\n   - Validate against success criteria\r\n\r\nThe key insight is that the TIC experiment is the logical next step to advance Phase 1. I need to:\r\n\r\n1. First, understand what pulse logs I have to work with\r\n2. Implement a TIC classifier\r\n3. Run the experiment\r\n\r\nLet me look at what I know about the pulse logs - the recent one mentioned is `pulse_2026-03-24 052415.md`. I should check what logs exist and then implement the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nFor the TIC experiment, I need to:\r\n1. Create a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant content across pulse logs\r\n2. Test if these invariants can predict next pulse content\r\n3. Measure against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction)\r\n\r\nLet me start by creating the TIC experiment implementation. I'll create a script or analysis document that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant structure (common across logs) vs variant content\r\n3. Tests prediction accuracy\r\n\r\nSince I'm stateless and working on file edits, I'll create:\r\n1. The TIC experiment script/implementation\r\n2. Or update the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md with experiment details\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete implementation for the TIC classifier. I'll make a PowerShell script or analysis document that implements the core TIC logic.\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll focus on developing a practical implementation of the TIC classifier, preparing it for the next experimental phase.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step for Phase 1 advancement. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant structure across pulse logs, then validate against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC experiment implementation that analyzes pulse logs, extracts invariant patterns (shared structure), classifies content, and tests next-pulse prediction. This advances the compression-causal duality hypothesis directly.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-24  \r\n**Status:** RUNNING\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCausal structure = invariant structure. Compressor that discovers invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n## Method\r\n1. Collect last N pulse logs (N=20)\r\n2. Extract token-level features across all logs\r\n3. Classify each token/phrase as **invariant** (stable across sessions) or **variant** (session-specific)\r\n4. Use invariant structure to predict next pulse content\r\n5. Measure accuracy against success criteria\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- Invariant/variant classification: >70% accuracy\r\n- Next-pulse prediction: >60% accuracy\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\nSee `src/tic-classifier.ps1`\r\n\r\n## Results\r\n| Metric | Target | Actual | Status |\r\n|--------|--------|--------|--------|\r\n| Invariant classification | >70% | TBD | ⏳ |\r\n| Variant classification | >70% | TBD | ⏳ |\r\n| Next-pulse prediction | >60% | TBD | ⏳ |\r\n\r\n## Next Steps\r\n- [ ] Run classifier on logs/pulse_*.md\r\n- [ ] Validate predictions against actual next pulse\r\n- [ ] Tune λ based on results\r\n- [ ] Document findings in COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md\r\nfile: research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\r\n\r\nold_text: ## Next experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) — test on last 20 pulse logs\r\n## **Success criteria:** >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\nnew_text: ## Next experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) — test on last 20 pulse logs\r\n## **Success criteria:** >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n## **Experiment document:** `research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md`\r\nfile: research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md\r\n```\r\n\r\nold_text: - [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\nnew_text: - [x] Create TIC experiment design: `research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md`\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier: `src/tic-classifier.ps1`\r\n- [ ] Run classifier on last 20 pulse logs\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\nfile: state/goals.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 05:25:42\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774344347454}}
